applyUsingCIEXYPolarThetaThenHistEq(ImageExt) - Method in class algorithms.imageProcessing.ImageSegmentation
applies a blue of sigma=1 to image, converts each pixel color to the polar angle of CIE XY Lab color space with an origin of (0.35, 0.35) and uses a histogram binning of kColors=8, then maps those bins to 0 to 255, then replaces a pixel if 7 or its neighbors have the same color, then applies histogram equalization to stretch the values to range 0 to 255.
applyUsingCIEXYPolarThetaThenHistEq(ImageExt, int, boolean) - Method in class algorithms.imageProcessing.ImageSegmentation
converts each pixel color to the polar angle of CIE XY Lab color space with an origin of (0.35, 0.35) and uses a histogram binning of kColors, then maps those bins to 0 to 255, then replaces a pixel if 7 or its neighbors have the same color, then applies histogram equalization to stretch the values to range 0 to 255.

applies a blur of sigma=1 to image, converts each pixel's color into CIE XY polar theta, then uses KMeansPlusPlus to create kColors=8 bins points then remaps the points to use the range 0 to 255, then replaces a pixel if it has 7 neighbors of same color, then applies histogram equalization to rescale the range to be between 0 and 255.

NOT READY FOR USE.
calculateUsingPolarCIEXYAndClustering(ImageExt, boolean) - Method in class algorithms.imageProcessing.ImageSegmentation
Calculates lists of black pixels, white pixels, grey pixels, and assigns the remaining to the polar angle of CIEXY Lab color space, then creates a map of the polar angles and the number of pixels with those angles (=frequency) and uses density based clustering (http://nking.github.io/two-point-correlation/) to find clusters in that space (polar CIEXY vs frequency), then merges pixels in the grey list with adjacent clusters if similar, and the final result is a list of pixel clusters, including the black and white and remaining grey.
calculateUsingPolarCIEXYAndFrequency(ImageExt, boolean) - Method in class algorithms.imageProcessing.ImageSegmentation
Calculates lists of black pixels, white pixels, grey pixels, and assigns the remaining to the polar angle of CIEXY Lab color space, then creates a map of the polar angles and the number of pixels with those angles (=frequency), then finds peaks in theta above a fraction =0.03 of max limit then groups all pixels in the map by proximity to the peak, then merges pixels in the grey list with adjacent clusters if similar, and the final result is a list of pixel clusters, including the black and white and remaining grey.
calculateUsingPolarCIEXYAndFrequency(ImageExt, float, boolean) - Method in class algorithms.imageProcessing.ImageSegmentation
Calculates lists of black pixels, white pixels, grey pixels, and assigns the remaining to the polar angle of CIEXY Lab color space, then creates a map of the polar angles and the number of pixels with those angles (=frequency), then finds peaks in theta above a fraction of max limit then groups all pixels in the map by proximity to the peak, then merges pixels in the grey list with adjacent clusters if similar, and the final result is a list of pixel clusters, including the black and white and remaining grey.

estimateNIterForFifteenPercentOutliersFor2Points(int) - Method in class algorithms.imageProcessing.util.RANSACAlgorithmIterations
The estimate assumes that at least 15 percent of the nPoints are true matches with points in another set of points and determines the number of iterations needed for a 95% certainty that 2 points drawn randomly from nPoints will all be "truly matchable" with points in set2 (whose characteristics are presumed to be similar).
estimateNIterForFiftyPercentOutliersFor7Points(int) - Method in class algorithms.imageProcessing.util.RANSACAlgorithmIterations
The estimate assumes that at least 50 percent of the nMatchedPoints are outliers and determines the number of iterations needed for a 95% certainty that 7 points drawn randomly from nMatchedPoints will all be "true" matches, that is, not outliers.
estimateNIterForFiftyPercentOutliersFor8Points(int) - Method in class algorithms.imageProcessing.util.RANSACAlgorithmIterations
The estimate assumes that at least 50 percent of the nMatchedPoints are outliers and determines the number of iterations needed for a 95% certainty that 8 points drawn randomly from nMatchedPoints will all be "true" matches, that is, not outliers.
estimateNIterForTwentyFivePercentOutliersFor8Points(int) - Method in class algorithms.imageProcessing.util.RANSACAlgorithmIterations
The estimate assumes that at least 25 percent of the nMatchedPoints are outliers and determines the number of iterations needed for a 95% certainty that 8 points drawn randomly from nMatchedPoints will all be "true" matches, that is, not outliers.
estimateNIterUsingStandardRANSACApproximation(double, int) - Method in class algorithms.imageProcessing.util.RANSACAlgorithmIterations
using estimates for the number of iterations required to lower the probability that a set of nSet inliers is not found to 1-0.95=0.05 from: http://6.869.csail.mit.edu/fa12/lectures/lecture13ransac/lecture13ransac.pdf Note: this assumes that the user's nPoints >> nIter.

PolarAngleMergeSort - Class in algorithms.compGeometry.convexHull
adapted from https://code.google.com/p/two-point-correlation/source/browse/src/test/java/algorithms/compGeometry/convexHull/ under MIT License (MIT), Nichole King 2013 The algorithm uses a merge sort which has a worse case runtime is O(N * log_2(N)), but also includes an additional set of operations to remove inner points with the same polar angle from P0.
